# SentinelAI Guardian — environment configuration.
# Everything works with NO keys (deterministic engine + rule-based copilot).
# Add keys to upgrade the AI Security Copilot to a real model.

# --- Option A: AWS Bedrock (preferred, matches the AWS architecture) ---
# BEDROCK_MODEL_ID=anthropic.claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022-v2:0
# AWS_REGION=us-east-1
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
# (also requires: pnpm add @aws-sdk/client-bedrock-runtime)

# --- Option B: Anthropic API (no AWS account needed) ---
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL_ID=claude-sonnet-4-6

# --- Real on-chain data (wallet health & approvals) ---
# Without this, wallet/approval views show an honest "configure a provider"
# state instead of any invented data.
# ALCHEMY_API_KEY=
# ALCHEMY_NETWORK=eth-mainnet   # e.g. eth-mainnet, base-mainnet, arb-mainnet

# --- Persistence: scan history & detected threats (Amazon DynamoDB) ---
# Reuses the AWS credentials above. Create a table whose partition key is `pk`
# (String) and sort key is `sk` (String), then set its name here.
# DYNAMODB_TABLE=SentinelAIGuardian

# --- Rate limiting (optional, recommended for public deploys) ---
# Without these, rate limiting is in-memory per serverless instance. Add an
# Upstash Redis (free tier) for accurate distributed limits across instances.
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=
